# WendyOS x86: /data encrypted with LUKS2, key sealed to the TPM (PCR 7).
# systemd-cryptsetup opens it at boot from the systemd-tpm2 token in the LUKS2
# header (no passphrase). Resolved by GPT PARTLABEL because luksFormat wipes the
# ext4 fs label but the partition name survives (same reason the rootfs uses
# root=PARTLABEL=). Options:
#   tpm2-device=auto  find the one TPM and unseal from the header token
#   headless          never prompt on a console that may be absent
#   nofail            a slot that cannot open (e.g. a changed PCR 7) does not block
#                     boot; recover with the recovery key
# First-boot creation/enrollment is done by data-enroll.service (10-enroll.conf
# orders it before this unlock). See docs/plans/x86-security.md.
data  /dev/disk/by-partlabel/data  -  tpm2-device=auto,headless,nofail
